3.1 Each Founder shall devote such time and attention to the business of the Company as is necessary to perform their role effectively.

3.2 **Specific Roles**:

{{#founders}}- **{{name}}** shall serve as {{role}}
{{/founders}}

3.3 The Founders acknowledge that roles may evolve as the Company grows and that flexibility and collaboration are essential to the Company's success.

3.4 **Full-Time Commitment**: [Each Founder agrees to work full-time for the Company / Founders acknowledge that [specify] will work part-time initially].

3.5 **Compensation**: Founders' initial compensation shall be:

{{#founders}}- **{{name}}**: {{#if salary}}{{salary}} per annum{{else}}Deferred until [funding milestone]{{/if}}
{{/founders}}

5.1 **Ordinary Decisions**: Day-to-day operational decisions shall be made by [simple majority / designated CEO].

5.2 **Reserved Matters**: The following decisions require [unanimous consent / [●]% majority] of the Founders:

   (a) Admission of new founders or equity holders;

   (b) Issuing new equity or securities convertible into equity;

   (c) Entering into debt arrangements over [amount];

   (d) Selling, disposing of, or encumbering material assets;

   (e) Changing the Company's core business or strategy;

   (f) Entering into related-party transactions;

   (g) Appointing or removing directors;

   (h) Declaring dividends or distributions;

   (i) Approving the annual budget and business plan;

   (j) Any merger, acquisition, or sale of the Company.

5.3 **Board Composition**: The Board shall initially consist of [all Founders / [●]]. Board decisions require [simple majority / unanimous consent].

5.4 **Deadlock**: In the event of deadlock on a Reserved Matter, the Founders shall [seek mediation / refer to an independent expert / [other mechanism]].

9.1 This Agreement shall continue in force until:

   (a) terminated by unanimous written agreement of all Founders;

   (b) the Company is wound up or dissolved;

   (c) only one Founder remains; or

   (d) the Company completes a [Series A / Series B] financing, at which point this Agreement shall be superseded by a Shareholders' Agreement.

9.2 Clauses [6, 8, 11] shall survive termination of this Agreement.
